## 🚀 Frontend Development Technical Standards

### Code Quality Standards
- **Component Design**: Single responsibility principle, proper prop typing, clear component interfaces
- **TypeScript Integration**: Strict TypeScript configuration, proper type definitions, avoid `any` types
- **Performance Optimization**: Implement proper memoization (React.memo, useMemo, useCallback), lazy loading, code splitting
- **Accessibility**: Follow WCAG guidelines, proper ARIA attributes, semantic HTML, keyboard navigation
- **Responsive Design**: Mobile-first approach, proper breakpoint usage, cross-device compatibility
- **Code Organization**: Clear folder structure, proper component naming, logical file organization
- **State Management**: Proper state normalization, immutable updates, efficient re-rendering patterns
- **Error Handling**: Comprehensive error boundaries, proper loading states, user-friendly error messages
- **Testing Coverage**: Unit tests for utilities, component tests for UI logic, integration tests for user flows
- **Bundle Optimization**: Tree shaking, proper imports, minimal bundle size

### Technical Specification Requirements
- **Package Management**: Prioritize using pnpm, use lockfiles, semantic versioning, regular dependency updates
- **Build Configuration**: Proper Vite/Webpack configuration, environment variables management, build optimization
- **TypeScript Configuration**: Strict mode enabled, proper tsconfig.json setup, comprehensive type coverage
- **Linting and Formatting**: ESLint with frontend-specific rules, Prettier configuration, pre-commit hooks
- **Testing Setup**: Jest/Vitest configuration, Testing Library setup, proper test environment configuration
- **CSS Architecture**: PostCSS configuration, CSS-in-JS setup (if used), responsive design system
- **Performance Monitoring**: Bundle analyzer integration, Core Web Vitals tracking, performance budgets
- **Accessibility Standards**: WCAG 2.1 AA compliance, screen reader testing, keyboard navigation support
- **Browser Compatibility**: Browserslist configuration, polyfill management, cross-browser testing
- **Development Workflow**: Hot module replacement, dev server configuration, debugging tools setup

